  <thing id="iUmDeardst" name="Dreadstorm" description="This vicious-looking pole-arm with a barbed and pitted head is one of the vile creations of the shadow-giant smith Larach-Umbriol. It was created as a twin to the cursed weapon that slew Gerrant of Gilboath, the Last Justicar of Muir. {i}Dreadstorm{/i} is a {i}+3 human bane wounding guisarme{/i}. Three times per day as a standard action, the wielder can activate a {i}blade barrier{/i} that completely surrounds the wielder in a 20-foot radius. This {i}blade barrier{/i} lasts up to 15 minutes but can be dismissed by the wielder as a free action. The {i}blade barrier{/i} deals 15d6 points of damage per round (DC 19 Reflex save for half) and provides the usual +4 bonus to AC and +2 bonus on Reflex saves on attacks made through it, though not the attacks of the wielder as long as he is attacking with {i}Dreadstorm{/i}.\n\n{b}Construction{/b}\n{b}Requirements{/b}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}blade barrier{/i}, {i}mage&apos;s sword{/i}, {i}summon monster I{/i} ; {b}Cost{/b} 117,309 gp" compset="MagicWep" summary="{i}Dreadstorm{/i} is a {i}+3 human bane wounding guisarme{/i}" uniqueness="unique">
