  <thing id="ioUmTeleTr" name="Teleport Trunks" description="These trunks always come in pairs. Each looks like an old wooden or hardened leather steamer trunk without a lock. They stand 2 feet high are 4 1/2 feet long and are 3 feet wide. They are nondescript until a creature climbs inside and the lid is closed. Upon doing so, that creature and all gear and objects up to its maximum load that will fit within the closed trunk, are instantly teleported as the {i}greater teleport{/i} spell to the interior of the other trunk in the pair. The other trunk must be closed and empty for this to function. The {i}teleport{/i} functions as long as both trunks on are on the same plane. The trunk can hold one Medium, four Small, eight Tiny, twenty-four diminutive, or one hundred forty-four Fine creatures. A Large creature can squeeze into the trunk with a successful DC 20 Escape Artist but can not bring any gear other than mundane, nonbulky clothing and a light weapon.  The trunk can function once every 10 minute up to 3 times per day.\n\n{b}Note{/b}: The trunks weigh 50 lb. each\n\n{b}Construction{/b}\n{b}Requirements{/b}:  Craft Wondrous Item, {i}greater teleport{/i}; {b}Cost{/b} 25,000 gp" compset="Wondrous">
